		<ul class='children'>
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-stas bypostauthor even depth-2" id="comment-2792">
				<div id="div-comment-2792" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<cite class="fn"><a href='http://www.loper-os.org' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Stanislav</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.loper-os.org/?p=55&amp;cpage=1#comment-2792">April 30, 2012 at 2:17 pm</a></div>

		<p>Dear Mike from Shreveport,</p>
<p><a href="http://www.loper-os.org/?p=47" rel="nofollow">I have great respect for Chuck Moore</a>, and love Forth.  But it is not a high-level programming language.  (However, <a href="http://www.yosefk.com/blog/my-history-with-forth-stack-machines.html" rel="nofollow">Forth is, perhaps, the greatest <i>low-level</i> language ever devised.</a>)</p>
<p>Yours,<br />
-Stanislav</p>

